# Naming Conventions

## File Names

All file names **must** use kebab-case (lowercase letters with hyphens as separators, no spaces or underscores).

*Example*: `user-profile.tsx`, `get-user-info.ts`

## Fields and Variables

All fields and variables **must** use camelCase (lowercase first word, subsequent words capitalized, no underscores).

*Example*: `userEmail`, `createdAt`, `stripeSessionId`

These conventions apply to all new code and when refactoring existing code within the project.

## Enum Values

All enumeration values **must** use UPPERCASE letters (e.g., `ACTIVE`, `PENDING`, `COMPLETED`).

This convention applies to every enum you define in the project to ensure consistency and readability.
